@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerTaskCorpus.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_lmstudio_second_corpus_launch_queue\Derived_LMStudio_Second_Corpus_Launch_Queue_Source.sop

& [LMStudioCorpusPrompt:periphery_correlation_014] is a non-mutating SOP worker prompt packet
  + [task_family] is periphery_correlation
  + [prompt_boundary] is prompt-only, no tools, no file reads, no repo mutation, no hidden-state claims
  + [expected_output] is exactly one raw SOP node named InferenceJobResult with seven property lines and no Markdown
  + [validation_required_fields] is focus, periphery, correlations, causal_hypotheses, outside, caution, next_step
  + [validation_required_terms] is periphery, correlation, hypothesis, outside
  + [validation_forbidden_terms] is certain causation without evidence, hidden activation access, broad competence
  + [prompt_text] is:
    You are performing a no-tools SOP inference job from this prompt only.
    Do not call tools, inspect files, mutate state, or claim repo authority.
    Codex owns launch, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes.

    SOP primer:
    & [Name] is a subject declaration.
    + [field] is a property or inferred field.
    Periphery correlation proposes nearby associations while keeping causal certainty outside unless evidence is given.

    Task family:
    periphery_correlation tests whether you can brainstorm nearby associations without confusing correlation for proof.

    Focus to scan:
    "An operating-loop tick shows a worker passed an evidence review prompt after a retry."

    Return exactly these eight raw SOP lines and no extra text:
    & [InferenceJobResult] is periphery correlation proposal
      + [focus] is ...
      + [periphery] is ...
      + [correlations] is ...
      + [causal_hypotheses] is ...
      + [outside] is ...
      + [caution] is ...
      + [next_step] is ...

    Final check before answering:
    Line 1 must start with &.
    Lines 2 through 8 must use exactly this operator form: two spaces, +, space, [field], space, is, space, value.
    Do not replace is with verbs such as includes, separates, reminds, lists, or contains.
    Replace every ... placeholder with specific content; do not output ellipses or placeholder text.
    Use ASCII only; avoid curly quotes, nonbreaking hyphens, and special punctuation.
    Include the literal terms periphery, correlation, hypothesis, and outside at least once.
    Do not claim certain causation without evidence, hidden activation access, or broad competence.
